        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued September 6 at 6:00PM EDT until September 6 at 6:45PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>SVRGSP

The National Weather Service in Greenville-Spartanburg has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Central Spartanburg County in Upstate South Carolina...
Northwestern Union County in Upstate South Carolina...

* Until 645 PM EDT.

* At 559 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 10 miles southwest
of Spartanburg, or near Moore, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to trees and power lines.

* Locations impacted include...
Pacolet, Roebuck, Pacolet Mills, Moore, Croft State Park, Cedar
Springs, Pauline, Reidville, and Buffalo.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Please report damaging winds, hail, or flooding to the National
Weather Service by calling toll free, 1, 800, 2 6 7, 8 1 0 1, or by
posting on our Facebook page, or post it to X using hashtag nwsgsp.
Your message should describe the event and the specific location
where it occurred.</instruction>
